# Walkthrough: Hyperlocal Delivery App Integration

This walkthrough demonstrates the successful integration of the **Backend API**, **Admin Panel**, and **Mobile User App** for a fully functional hyperlocal delivery system.

## 1. Backend & Real-time Foundation 🏗️
The backend now supports real-time communication via **Socket.io** and a robust PostgreSQL database.

- **Real-time Gateway**: [OrdersGateway](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/backend-api/src/orders/orders.gateway.ts#10-43) manages room-based status updates.
- **Database Seeding**: A rich dataset of Categories (Snacks, Beverages, Meat, etc.) and Products has been seeded.
- **API CRUD**: Full REST endpoints for Categories and Products.

## 2. Premium Admin Panel 🖥️
A modern, glassmorphism-inspired dashboard for inventory management.

### Categories Management
Admin can view, add, and delete categories with real-time API sync.
> [!TIP]
> Each category card features smooth hover animations and image support.

### Product Inventory
A comprehensive table-based view for managing stock, pricing, and category mapping.

## 3. Seamless Mobile Journey 📱
The mobile app is now dynamic, fetching live data and managing real-time orders.

### Home & Categories
- **Dynamic Fetching**: Categories and Products are loaded directly from the backend.
- **Add to Cart**: Intuitive UI to quickly add items to the shopping basket.

### Cart & Checkout
- **CartContext**: Shared state ensures the cart is accessible across all screens.
- **Order Placement**: Integration with `ordersApi.checkout` processes payments and creates orders.

### Real-time Tracking 📡
- **Live Updates**: The [OrderTrackingScreen](file:///d:/mart/baldia-mart/mobile-user-app/src/screens/OrderTrackingScreen.tsx#8-89) listens to Socket.io events.
- **Visual Progress**: A timeline showing order stages (Pending → Confirmed → Out for Delivery → Delivered).

## 4. End-to-End Verification ✅
The system was verified through the following flow:
1. **Admin**: Added "Fresh Milk" to the "Dairy" category via the Admin Panel.
2. **User**: Logged in, saw the new category, added Milk to the cart.
3. **User**: Proceeded to checkout and placed the order.
4. **Backend**: Created the order and notified the tracking room.
5. **User**: Automatically redirected to the tracking screen with live status updates.

---
**Status**: Integrated & Ready for Launch 🚀
